---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import TimezoneMapStrip from '../components/TimezoneMapStrip.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Time Zone Map — World Time Zones at a Glance | Clockr"
	description="See what time it is around the world at a glance. Interactive UTC offset strip from UTC−12 to UTC+14 with live times and your zone highlighted."
	category="timezones"
>
	<div class="tzm-page">
		<div class="tzm-header">
			<div class="tzm-eyebrow">🌍 Time Zones</div>
			<h1 class="tzm-title">
				<span class="tzm-gradient">Time Zone Map</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="tzm-subtitle">See what time it is around the world at a glance</p>
		</div>

		<TimezoneMapStrip client:load />

		<section class="tzm-how">
			<h2 class="tzm-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="tzm-how-card">
				<p>
					The Earth is divided into time zones — offset bands measured from UTC
					(Coordinated Universal Time), the global reference clock. Each zone is
					roughly 15 degrees of longitude wide, though political borders and
					historical choices mean real zones do not follow neat meridian lines.
					This page shows a simplified strip from UTC−12 to UTC+14 with major
					cities in each band.
				</p>
				<p>
					Each block displays the current wall-clock time for that UTC offset,
					updating every second in your browser. Clockr detects your IANA time
					zone automatically and highlights the matching band. Tap or click any
					zone to expand a panel with representative cities, their live local
					times, and today&apos;s date — powered by the same Intl API used on our
					World Clock.
				</p>
				<p>
					This is a reference visualization, not a geographic map. Fractional
					offsets such as UTC+5:30 (India) and UTC+5:45 (Nepal) appear as
					separate bands because some countries align clocks to the sun rather
					than whole-hour meridians. Daylight saving can shift cities between
					bands seasonally — the highlight always reflects your offset right now.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="tzm-faq">
			<h2 class="tzm-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="tzm-faq-list">
				<details class="tzm-faq-item">
					<summary class="tzm-faq-question">What is UTC?</summary>
					<div class="tzm-faq-answer">
						<p>
							UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) is the international standard that
							all time zones are measured against. It replaced GMT as the
							primary reference in 1972 and is kept precise using atomic clocks.
							When a zone is labeled UTC+9, local time is nine hours ahead of
							UTC; UTC−5 is five hours behind. See our UTC/GMT Converter for
							direct conversions.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tzm-faq-item">
					<summary class="tzm-faq-question"
						>Why do some time zones have unusual offsets like UTC+5:45?</summary
					>
					<div class="tzm-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Most zones differ from UTC by whole hours, but some countries chose
							fractional offsets to better match local solar noon. Nepal uses
							UTC+5:45 — a quarter-hour ahead of India&apos;s UTC+5:30 — and
							Chatham Islands use UTC+12:45 in summer. Iran (UTC+3:30) and
							Newfoundland (UTC−3:30) follow the same logic with half-hour steps.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tzm-faq-item">
					<summary class="tzm-faq-question"
						>How is my time zone detected?</summary
					>
					<div class="tzm-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Your browser reports an IANA time zone identifier (such as
							<code>Europe/London</code> or <code>America/New_York</code>)
							through the Intl API. Clockr calculates your current UTC offset
							from that identifier and highlights the matching band on the strip.
							No location permission is requested — only the time zone setting
							your device already uses.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tzm-faq-item">
					<summary class="tzm-faq-question"
						>Why does my highlighted zone change in summer?</summary
					>
					<div class="tzm-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Countries that observe daylight saving time shift their clocks by
							one hour for part of the year. London moves from UTC+0 (GMT) to
							UTC+1 (BST); New York moves from UTC−5 to UTC−4. The highlight
							follows your actual offset at this moment, so it will jump between
							adjacent bands when clocks change.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tzm-faq-item">
					<summary class="tzm-faq-question"
						>How many time zones are there?</summary
					>
					<div class="tzm-faq-answer">
						<p>
							There are 24 principal meridian-based hours, but political and
							fractional zones bring the total to about 38 distinct UTC offsets
							in use today, spanning UTC−12 through UTC+14. This map shows the
							most commonly referenced bands; our World Clock lists live times
							for 200+ individual cities.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="tzm-related">
			<h3 class="tzm-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="tzm-related-grid">
				<a href="/world-clock" class="tzm-related-card"
					><span class="tzm-related-name">World Clock</span></a
				>
				<a href="/timezone-converter" class="tzm-related-card"
					><span class="tzm-related-name">Timezone Converter</span></a
				>
				<a href="/timezone-abbreviations" class="tzm-related-card"
					><span class="tzm-related-name">Time Zone Abbreviations</span></a
				>
				<a href="/time-zones" class="tzm-related-card"
					><span class="tzm-related-name">All Time Zone Tools</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.tzm-tool {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	.tzm-user-banner {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 10px 20px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 32px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1);
	}

	.tzm-user-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.85);
		width: 100%;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.tzm-user-location {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.tzm-user-time {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-user-offset {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
	}

	.tzm-hint {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 20px;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.tzm-strip-wrap {
		overflow-x: auto;
		padding-bottom: 8px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
		scrollbar-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4) transparent;
	}

	.tzm-strip {
		display: flex;
		gap: 10px;
		min-width: min-content;
		padding: 4px 2px 12px;
	}

	.tzm-band {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		width: 132px;
		min-height: 140px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 6px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		cursor: pointer;
		text-align: left;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease,
			transform 0.15s ease;
		position: relative;
	}

	.tzm-band:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
	}

	.tzm-band--user {
		border-color: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.75);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.2);
	}

	.tzm-band--selected {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.85);
		box-shadow: 0 0 28px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.25);
	}

	.tzm-band--user.tzm-band--selected {
		border-color: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.95);
		box-shadow: 0 0 32px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.3);
	}

	.tzm-band-you {
		position: absolute;
		top: 8px;
		right: 8px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: #ec4899;
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.5);
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 2px 6px;
	}

	.tzm-band-offset {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 800;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-band-time {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 22px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -0.5px;
		color: #fff;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.tzm-band-cities {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.42);
		line-height: 1.4;
		margin-top: auto;
	}

	.tzm-detail {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.25);
		border-radius: 18px;
		padding: 24px;
		animation: tzm-detail-in 0.25s ease;
	}

	@keyframes tzm-detail-in {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translateY(8px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	.tzm-detail-header {
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		padding-bottom: 18px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
	}

	.tzm-detail-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-detail-regions {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 14px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-now {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 12px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tzm-detail-clock {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.tzm-detail-date {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	.tzm-detail-cities {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.12);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city--user {
		border-color: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.45);
		box-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.1);
	}

	.tzm-detail-city-top {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 10px;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-flag {
		font-size: 22px;
		line-height: 1;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city-country {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
		margin-top: 2px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-you-badge {
		margin-left: auto;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: #ec4899;
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.4);
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 3px 8px;
		white-space: nowrap;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city-time {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -0.5px;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	.tzm-detail-city-date {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.tzm-band {
			width: 118px;
			min-height: 128px;
		}

		.tzm-band-time {
			font-size: 20px;
		}
	}
</style>

<style>
	.tzm-page {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px 80px;
	}

	.tzm-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 40px;
	}

	.tzm-eyebrow {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tzm-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tzm-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tzm-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tzm-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tzm-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.tzm-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.tzm-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.tzm-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tzm-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.tzm-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.tzm-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.tzm-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tzm-faq-item[open] .tzm-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.tzm-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.tzm-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tzm-faq-answer code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.9);
	}

	.tzm-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.tzm-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tzm-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.tzm-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.tzm-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tzm-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
	}

	.tzm-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}
</style>
